               <msContents>
                  <summary>I) Gadla Ṣadǝqan [za-Bāraknāhā] “Vita of the Righteous Ones
                     [za-Bāraknāhā]” (fols. 1ra-6ra [explicit], 9ra [incipit]-17rb), misplaced&#xD;
                     II) Mälkǝʾa Ṣadǝqan [za-Bāraknāhā] “Image of the Righteous Ones [za-Bāraknāhā]”
                     (fols. 6rb-8vb)&#xD; &#xD; Colophon.</summary>
                  <msItem xml:id="ms_i1">

                     <incipit>
                        <foreign xml:lang="en"/>
                     </incipit>
                     <explicit>
                        <foreign xml:lang="en"/>
                     </explicit>
                     <note/>
                  </msItem>
                  <!--The data in the items below refers to other items. please remove this items and move the information to the appropriate place.-->
                  <msItem xml:id="ms_i2">
                     <note>Texts I and II are the same as Texts I and II in Ms.<ref type="mss" corresp="ESdsm017">DSM-017</ref>.</note>
                     <note/>
                     <note>Text I:</note>
                     <note>- Text I is the same text as the one included in the Ms. from the church
                        of Bāraknāhā (Eritrea) and published by C. CONTI ROSSINI in Ricordi di un
                        soggiorno in Eritrea, Asmara 1903, 7-22. However, in<ref type="mss" corresp="ESmy026">MY-026</ref>a the text is slightly shorter: the final
                        part (from <locus target="#6ra">6ra</locus> l.11) which corresponds in the
                        Conti Rossini’s edition pp. 21 l.12-22 l.27 is missing.</note>
                     <note>- Due to the condition of the Ms., the text is in disarray: the incipit
                        is on <locus target="#9r">9r</locus> (first fol. of quire II); after <locus target="#16vb">16vb</locus> (last fol. of quire II) it continues on
                           <locus target="#1r">1r</locus> (first fol. of quire I) till <locus target="#6rb">6rb</locus>.</note>
                     <note/>
                     <note>Text II:</note>
                     <note>- Due to the condition of the Ms., the incipit of the text, as well as
                        other passages, is not readable, and the sequence and exact number of the
                        strophes are not known.</note>
                  </msItem>
                  <colophon xml:id="coloph1">
                     <locus target="#6ra">6ra</locus> l.11: ዛ{ቲ፡} መጽሐፍ፡ ተፈጸመ፡ ገ{ድ}ሎሙ፡ ለጻድቃን፨ ዘደብረ፡
                     ማዕጾ፨ ዘአልቦሙ፡ ኍልቈ፡ በረከተ፡ ፀሎቶሙ፡ ወሐብተ፡ ረድኤቶሙ፡ ለኵሎሙ፡ ጻድቃን፨ ምስሌሆሙ፡ ይደ[sic]ምረነ፡ ኢየሱስ፡
                     ክርስቶስ፡ ምስለ፡ ፍቁሮሙ፡ አቍባ፡ ሚካኤል፡ ወለጸሓፊ[፡] &lt;...&gt; The colophon mentions ʾAqʷǝba
                     Mikāʾel, probably the donor, and to the scribe, whose name, however, is not
                     readable. The book is entitled “Gadla Ṣādǝqān za-Dabra Maʿṣo”, “Vita of the
                     Righteous Ones of Dabra Maʿṣo”. The conclusion in column b is not readable.
                  </colophon>
