                  <handDesc>
                     <!--ACHTUNG! first HandNote comes from writing system in Ethiospare. the others are one for each CHANGE OF HAND-->
                     <handNote xml:id="h1" script="Ethiopic">
                        <seg type="script">Crude, irregular.</seg>
                        <seg type="ink">Black; red (brilliant vermillion).</seg>The name of the
                        scribe is mentioned in the colophon but is not readable because of the
                        condition of the Ms.<date>19th century (?)</date>
                        <seg type="rubrication">Nomina sacra; name of the donor and scribe.&#xD;
                           Groups of lines, alternating with black lines, in the incipit page of
                           Text I and in the incipit of Text II; the beginning of some paragraphs in
                           Text I (s. fols. 1ra, 2ra); the words salām and Ṣādǝqān (ʾo-Ṣādǝqān) in
                           Text II.&#xD; Some corrections interlineally and lines marking erasures;
                           elements of the punctuation signs and of Ethiopic numerals.</seg>
                     </handNote>
                     <handNote xml:id="h2" script="Ethiopic">The script is angular. The quality of
                        the hand (orientation of the letters, size, thickness) varies throughout the
                        Ms.<!--The names of this hands need to be replaced by appropriate refs.--></handNote>
                     <handNote xml:id="h3" script="Ethiopic"> - the letter ጵ has the 6th order
                        marker oriented to the right, set up on the vertical stroke at the top
                           (<locus target="#1ra">1ra</locus>
                        l.17).<!--The names of this hands need to be replaced by appropriate refs.--></handNote>
                  </handDesc>
